                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24580/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-15T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 15, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>324. Your 540, April 6, 4 p.m. War Department states that all United States
                    military activities in North Africa are under the command of General Maxwell
                    with the exception of the policy and operational control of the Ferry Command
                    which that Department desires to maintain in Washington and the duties of the
                    Military Attaché. There is no prospect at present of any change in this
                    arrangement.</p>
                <p>With reference to Colonel Fellers, the War Department asserts that no actual
                    military operations are contemplated at present.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
